summary: FCSTANDARD/32 is an intelligence source or asset who has been in contact with a CIA Case Officer (C/O) or staff member in Addis Ababa. These contacts, summarized in cables and messages dated February 25, 1998, cover a range of topics including Sudan, Libya, and the presence of Israeli and Russian delegations. FCSTANDARD/32 provides information about individuals, activities, and security measures, offering potential leads and insights for ongoing intelligence operations. The summaries also include personal details and observations made by FCSTANDARD/32.
significance: The provided documents do not indicate any connection to the JFK assassination. FCSTANDARD/32 appears to be an intelligence source providing information on various topics of interest to the CIA in Addis Ababa.
